chmod [args] - 'change mode' comes with arguments

1. First Argument - 'u' for user, 'g' for group, 'o' for others
		  - also can be used for multiple (ug, ugo)

2. Using '+' for adding
	 '-' for removing
	 '=' for assigning a Permission

3. Second Argument right after +, - or + 
	- speciify permission r, w or x or multiple permission like rw or rx

4. Third Argument - name of the file whose permissions are to be changed

eg. chmod u+x abc.txt
    chmod ugo+rwx abc.txt 
    chmod ug+rw,o-x abc.txt	    //adds r & w permission for user & group and removes x permission for others

**shell script file without execution permission can be run by 
>> sh xyz.sh      or 
>> bash xyz.sh


